The Herald Arts Reporter Culture Fund of Zimbabwe Trustâ€™s CreativeACTIONs, supported by the European Union Delegation to Zimbabwe, today launched its second call for proposals to strengthen capacities for Zimbabwean artists, cultural practitioners and institutions, creative civil society organisations, private operators involved in creative industries, arts associations and professional networks as well as arts education institutions. CreativeACTIONs aims to facilitate and strengthen the growth of Zimbabwe creative sector and their capacities to promote equitable access and inclusive participation. Projects implemented in the digital environment but impacting a diverse and wide range of publics will receive special consideration. Only project proposals containing activities that fully comply with the COVID-19 guidelines and demonstrate adaptability to different stages of the lockdown measures by the Government will be considered. Project proposals may be submitted along the following guidelines; LOT 1: Minimum of US$6 000 and a maximum amount of US$50 000. LOT 2: Minimum of US$500 and a maximum amount of US$5 000. The deadline for submission of proposals 11 March 2021 at 5pm.